This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and specifically with unsupervised constituency parsing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it uses deep learning techniques to learn representations and induce trees. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it uses neural networks, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) because it uses dynamic programming, which is a common technique in computer vision.
